description.plain: Knocked Loose is an American hardcore band from Oldham County, Kentucky, formed in 2013 and currently signed to Pure Noise Records. Knocked Loose began in 2013 with the release of an EP titled Pop Culture on Little Heart Records. In 2015, Knocked Loose released a split with Damaged Goods on No Luck Records. In 2016, the band announced their first studio album, titled Laugh Tracks, which was released on September 16, 2016.

description.plain:
Lead singer Bryan Garris states in an interview that this track was inspired by events like the death of Prince. When a celebrity dies, people all of a sudden feel this personal connection to them–like they lost someone that they really know.

Bryan rejects the sentiment as fake feeling and a false emotional response.
